reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 18, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Fantastic Multivitamin Pack and Value
reviews.reviewText: I'm 45 and over the years, I've tried A LOT of multivitamins and multivitamin packs. Some weren't very good at all and some were good, but overpriced and I think that's the main problem with most vitamin packs on the market today. That's where Planet 3 Vitamins - Core Supplement Pack comes into play. You get a great quality multivitamin pack at a VERY reasonable price. At the time of this review (1/17/24) I just finished my first month of being on them yesterday and I'm definitely feeling better on them than I did off of them. In fact, I feel good enough that the Planet 3 Vitamins - Core Supplement Pack is the ONLY product that I've subscribed to for automatic monthly delivery and that's saying something. They are DEFINITELY worth a try.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on April 17, 2022
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars I Love These Vitamins! High Quality and Super Convenient.
reviews.reviewText: I’ve been taking vitamins regularly for many years now, so I know the difference between “okay vitamins” and “high quality” vitamins — and these are high quality. I noticed many of the minerals in this formulation are “chelated” which I’m surprised the manufacturer doesn’t point out. Chelated minerals are better absorbed by the body. They do point out that the Omega-3 capsule is sustainably sourced and enteric coated. Many people don’t know what enteric coating is… it’s a process of providing an extra coating on the capsule so it dissolves farther down in the digestive system. This is great for me because when I take my vitamins with a little bit of food, I don’t get any bad taste or odor.Bottom line, I switched to this product primarily because of the quality. Then, when you talk about convenience, it’s a no brainer. I was already taking several of these vitamins anyway and had a bunch of bottles at both my home in the city and at my lake house. Now I just keep a box at each place, and it makes it easy not to forget to take them. Every morning I take them with breakfast and start the day feeling great. I eat pretty healthy, but I consider these vitamin packs a little insurance plan that I get everything that I need.(If you’re on the fence about trying them, once you do try them, you’ll never go back to a bunch of bottled vitamins.)
